(235, 'Resolution 21 (Cg-18)', 'Resolution 21 (Cg-18)', 'https://library.wmo.int/doc_num.php?explnum_id=9827/#page=92', 92, 'Implementation of the Global Framework for Climate Services ', '', '2019', 'Cg', '18', 'Resolution', '', 'LTG1-Services', 'SO1.2-Climate and agrometeorological services', 'GFCS - Global Framework for Climate Services', '', 'Climate', 'S - Services Department', 'CS - Climate Services Branch', 'Climate services have been integrated into SERCOM through the Standing Committee on Climate Services. The GFCS Partners Advisory Committee has identified priorities and drafted terms of reference, which are included in draft decision 5.6(2), submitted to EC-73 through the TCC as Doc. 5.6(2).', 'Keep in force'),
(236, 'Resolution 22 (Cg-18)', 'Resolution 22 (Cg-18)', 'https://library.wmo.int/doc_num.php?explnum_id=9827/#page=95', 95, 'Manual on High quality Global Data Management Framework for Climate', '', '2019', 'Cg', '18', 'Resolution', '', 'LTG1-Services', 'SO1.2-Climate and agrometeorological services', 'GFCS - Global Framework for Climate Services', '', 'Climate', 'S - Services Department', 'CS - Climate Services Branch', 'The Manual on High Quality Global Data Management Framework for Climate has been published (WMO-No. 1238). The process of the update of the manual started and will continue in collaboration between INFCOM and SERCOM. The support of a reference open-source data management System has been initiated and being funded.', 'Suppress'),
