(238, 'Resolution 24 (Cg-18)', 'Resolution 24 (Cg-18)', 'https://library.wmo.int/doc_num.php?explnum_id=9827/#page=98', 98, 'Vision, strategy and organizational arrangements for hydrology and water resources in WMO ', '', '2019', 'Cg', '18', 'Resolution', '', 'LTG5-Governance', 'Policy requiring coordination', 'Hydrology', '', 'Water and cryosphere', 'W - Hydrology and Cryosphere Coordination', '', 'Recommendation to Congress for the adoption of the Action plan is contained in Draft Recommendation 3.3(1)/1 (EC-73). Will be finalized by Cg-Ext. (2021). ToR of the Hydrological Assembly and definition of operational hydrology to be maintained until future amendment. All other actions completed, in particular HCP has been established, met in December 2019 and November 2020 and has been working remotely since then.', 'Keep in force'),
(239, 'Resolution 25 (Cg-18)', 'Resolution 25 (Cg-18)', 'https://library.wmo.int/doc_num.php?explnum_id=9827/#page=103', 103, 'Major hydrological initiatives ', '', '2019', 'Cg', '18', 'Resolution', '', 'LTG5-Governance', 'Policy requiring coordination', 'Hydrology', '', 'Water and cryosphere', 'W - Hydrology and Cryosphere Coordination', '', 'The continuity of the 8 major hydrological initiatives is being ensured by assigning the responsibility of each of them to various Standing Committees of the two TCs, under the coordination of HCP. Work to implement ambition 8 on water quality is under way.', 'Keep in force'),
(240, 'Resolution 26 (Cg-18)', 'Resolution 26 (Cg-18)', 'https://library.wmo.int/doc_num.php?explnum_id=9827/#page=105', 105, 'Provision of impact-based forecast and warning services in an innovative and integrated way ', '', '2019', 'Cg', '18', 'Resolution', '', 'LTG1-Services', 'SO1.1-Disaster risk reduction and public services', 'Multi-hazard', '', '', 'S - Services Department', 'DPS -Disaster Risk Reduction and Public Services Branch', 'SERCOM ET-GSD composition being finalized. ET-GSD ToRs were based on this resolution: Contribution to guidance on the use of GIS-based formats, Artificial Intelligence, Big Data, and the inclusion of data from innovative sources, in collaboration with INFCOM, SG-HEA, SG-ENE and SG-URB included in the TORs of ET-GSD.', 'Keep in force'),
