(253, 'Resolution 39 (Cg-18)', 'Resolution 39 (Cg-18)', 'https://library.wmo.int/doc_num.php?explnum_id=9827/#page=138', 138, 'Establishment of collaboration between the International Air Transport Association and WMO on the development and operation of the Aircraft Meteorological Data Relay Programme', '', '2019', 'Cg', '18', 'Resolution', '', 'LTG2-Infrastructure', 'SO2.1-Observations', 'Observing systems and networks', 'Aircraft-based observations', 'Aviation', 'I - Infrastructure Department', 'ONM - Observing Networks and Measurement Division', 'WMO and IATA have signed a new Working Arrangement on AMDAR development under WICAP; The establishment of regional AMDAR programs is in progress in accordance with the Implementation Plan; WICAP Governing Board has been formed. EC and INFCOM now have responsibility for the implementation; Implementation has been delayed due to COVID crisis and WMO reorganization but is in progress.', 'Suppress'),
(254, 'Resolution 40 (Cg-18)', 'Resolution 40 (Cg-18)', 'https://library.wmo.int/doc_num.php?explnum_id=9827/#page=144', 144, 'Members’ contribution to the actions specified in the Implementation Plan for the Evolution of Global Observing Systems in the context of the future WMO Integrated Global Observing System implementation plan ', '', '2019', 'Cg', '18', 'Resolution', '', 'LTG2-Infrastructure', 'SO2.1-Observations', 'WIGOS - WMO Integrated Global Observing System', 'Capability, design, evolution, implementation and monitoring', '', 'I - Infrastructure Department', 'WIGOS - WMO Integrated Observing System (WIGOS) Branch', 'INFCOM is developing high-level guidance document on Members\' response to WIGOS Vision 2040 during 2020-2023 to be submitted via INFCOM-2. In the meantime, this one should remain in force.', 'Keep in force'),
(255, 'Resolution 41 (Cg-18)', 'Resolution 41 (Cg-18)', 'https://library.wmo.int/doc_num.php?explnum_id=9827/#page=146', 146, 'Use of the Observing Systems Capability Analysis and Review Tool surface component (OSCAR/Surface) for the collection and recording of the WMO Integrated Global Observing System metadata ', '', '2019', 'Cg', '18', 'Resolution', '', 'LTG2-Infrastructure', 'SO2.1-Observations', 'WIGOS - WMO Integrated Global Observing System', 'Capability, design, evolution, implementation and monitoring', '', 'I - Infrastructure Department', 'WIGOS - WMO Integrated Observing System (WIGOS) Branch', 'The following related document is submitted to EC-73: Draft Resolution 4.2(6)/1 (EC-73) - Guide to the WMO Integrated Global Observing System (WMO-No. 1165); Furthermore, learning material on OSCAR/Surface has been further developed and made available through the WIGOS Learning Portal in Moodle, as well as regular webinars have been delivered; The tool is also being further developed to facilitate users’ interaction with new releases launched twice per year, including new features. Keep in force.', 'Keep in force'),
(256, 'Resolution 42 (Cg-18)', 'Resolution 42 (Cg-18)', 'https://library.wmo.int/doc_num.php?explnum_id=9827/#page=147', 147, 'Radio frequencies for meteorological and related environmental activities', '', '2019', 'Cg', '18', 'Resolution', '', 'LTG2-Infrastructure', 'SO2.1-Observations', '', '', '', 'I - Infrastructure Department', '', 'WMO Position on radiofrequency matters has been presented to WRC-19, in 2019. WMO Draft position paper for WRC-23 prepared by ET-RFC and endorsed by INFCOM I part 2. To be further reviewed and updated before WRC-23, which takes place in 2023. Handbook “Use of Radio Spectrum for Meteorology: Weather, Water and Climate Monitoring and Prediction” is maintained and published as required.', 'Suppress'),
(257, 'Resolution 43 (Cg-18)', 'Resolution 43 (Cg-18)', 'https://library.wmo.int/doc_num.php?explnum_id=9827/#page=149', 149, 'Report of the seventeenth session of the Commission for Instruments and Methods of Observation ', '', '2019', 'Cg', '18', 'Resolution', '', 'LTG2-Infrastructure', 'SO2.1-Observations', 'Measurement, instruments and traceability', '', '', 'I - Infrastructure Department', 'ONM - Observing Networks and Measurement Division', 'Report published as WMO-No. 1227. Some actions are completed others still being dealt with by INFCOM.', 'Keep in force'),
(258, 'Resolution 44 (Cg-18)', 'Resolution 44 (Cg-18)', 'https://library.wmo.int/doc_num.php?explnum_id=9827/#page=152', 152, 'Joint World Meteorological Organization-Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission of UNESCO Strategy for Marine Meteorological and Oceanographic Data Management (2018-2021) ', '', '2019', 'Cg', '18', 'Resolution', '', 'LTG2-Infrastructure', 'SO2.2-Data', 'Ocean data', '', 'Ocean', 'I - Infrastructure Department', 'DIM - Data and Information Management Division', 'SG-OOIS is charged to identify functional connections of the ocean observations and data related activities including Data strategy. Work is progressing within SG-OOIS.', 'Keep in force'),
(259, 'Resolution 45 (Cg-18)', 'Resolution 45 (Cg-18)', 'https://library.wmo.int/doc_num.php?explnum_id=9827/#page=154', 154, 'Ensuring adequate marine meteorological and oceanographic observations and data coverage for the safety of navigation and the protection of life and property in coastal and offshore areas ', '', '2019', 'Cg', '18', 'Resolution', '', 'LTG2-Infrastructure', 'SO2.2-Data', 'Ocean data', '', 'Ocean', 'I - Infrastructure Department', 'ESM - Earth System Monitoring Division', 'Work is underway through OCG networks to collect oceanographic variables, the observation of which is critical for the safety of navigation and the protection of life and property in coastal and offshore areas. Relaying the Resolution to the United Nations General Assembly for its consideration by the Secretary-General is yet to be completed.', 'Keep in force'),
